@yegor256 @longtimeago 
In my opinion, MkStorage.lock() will take an lock on a process in current thread. silently wait if a lock has already been taken. 

if other thread try to take lock,  system should wait and retry X times. 
if still can not get lock after attempted X times, system should throw concurrency exception.

In MkStorage.unlock(), system will release lock and other ones can take lock and process.

@yegor256 I'm not sure that's your expectation. Please correct me if i'm wrong. Thanks
